I agree with Tom. Our first bus was a brand new 64 and it was the station
wagon of choice for a farm family with (then) seven kids. My dad had his
severe words with it and the 40 hp motor which was repaired twice and
replaced with a 1300 later. It was the primary vehicle and it took us to the
grocery store, camping and hunting, and on a long vacation once. The
nostalgia never wore off and I have been working on them (engine wise) since
1969. People I know don't know me in anything else but a VW of some model.

67 Single Cab, DP 1641cc 34PICT-3 
